%N A348175 Irregular table T(n, k) read by rows: T(n, k) = T(n-1, k/2) when k is even and 3*T(n-1, k-1)/2) + 2^(n-1) when k is odd. T(0, 0) = 0 and 0 <= k <= 2^n-1.
%C A348175 Positive terms are from A213539. - Thomas Scheuerle, Sep 25 2025
%H A348175 <a href="/index/3#3x1">Index entries for sequences related to 3x+1 (or Collatz) problem</a>
%F A348175 T(n, k) = T(n-1, k/2) for k being even.
%F A348175 T(n, k) = 3*T(n-1, (k-1)/2) + 2^(n-1) for k being odd.
%F A348175 T(n, k) = 2*T(n-1, k) for 0 <= k <= 2^(n-1) - 1.
%F A348175 T(n, k) = Sum_{i=0..r} 2^(n-1-e[i]) * 3^i where binary expansion k = 2^e[0] + 2^e[1] + ... + 2^e[r] with ascending e[0] < e[1] < ... < e[r] (A133457). - _Kevin Ryde_, Oct 22 2021
%F A348175 From _Thomas Scheuerle_, Sep 24 2025: (Start)
%F A348175 T(n, k) = A119733(A030109(2^n+k)).
%F A348175 Consider the triangle of signed rational numbers
%F A348175 M(n, k) = (C*2^n - T(n, k))/3^A000120(k), with C=2:
%F A348175 n\k|   0|   1|   2|   3|   4|   5|   6|   7
%F A348175 0  |   2|    |    |    |    |    |    |
%F A348175 1  |   4|   1|    |    |    |    |    |
%F A348175 2  |   8|   2| 7/3| 1/3|    |    |    |
%F A348175 3  |  16|   4|14/3| 2/3|   5|   1|11/9|-1/9
%F A348175 Each row n contains all possible start values to reach C=2 in n steps, where each step may be either the operation k_{m+1} = k_{m}/2 or k_{m+1} = (3*k_{m}+1)/2. The positive integers in row n are the start values to reach C=2 in n iterations of the Collatz map A014682. We may replace C by any other integer >=2 here.
%F A348175 A strengthened version of the Collatz conjecture asserts that all rational numbers of the form b/3^e appear eventually in this triangle.
%F A348175 M(n+1, k)     = 2*M(n, k).
%F A348175 M(n+2, 4*k-3) =   M(n, k). (End)
%e A348175 n\k 0  1  2  3  4  5  6  7
%e A348175 0   0
%e A348175 1   0  1
%e A348175 2   0  2  1  5
%e A348175 3   0  4  2 10  1  7  5 19
%t A348175 T[0, 0] = 0; T[n_, k_] := T[n, k] = If[EvenQ[k], T[n - 1, k/2], 3*T[n - 1, (k - 1)/2] + 2^(n - 1)]; Table[T[n, k], {n, 0, 5}, {k, 0, 2^n - 1}] // Flatten (* _Amiram Eldar_, Oct 11 2021 *)
%o A348175 (PARI) T(n, k) = if ((n==0) && (k==0), 0, if (k%2, 3*T(n-1,(k-1)/2) + 2^(n-1), T(n-1,k/2)));
%o A348175 tabf(nn) = for (n=0, nn, for (k=0, 2^n-1, print1(T(n,k), ", ")); print); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Oct 18 2021
%o A348175 (PARI) T(n, k) = my(ret=0); for(i=0, n-1, if(bittest(k, n-1-i), ret=3*ret+1<<i)); ret; \\ _Kevin Ryde_, Oct 22 2021
